reviewText: The Delta State was a dark and intriguing French-Canadian production (English dialogue).  4 young people awake in a psychic research facility with no memory of how they got there, but with psychic powers.  They are taken under the wing of Brodie, a shadowy figure with some kind of spying background, to fight a psychic threat to the entire human race-- an alien enemy who invades the human subconscious.  The series chronicles both their battles, and their efforts to figure out who they are and where they came from.
